      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(feishu): fall back to post mode when markdown tables exceed card limit",
        "body": "## Problem\n\nWhen an agent generates a reply containing more than 5 Markdown tables, the Feishu plugin detects tables and sends the message as an interactive card. However, Feishu cards have a hard limit of **5 table components** per card (`ErrCode: 11310; card table number over limit`). Messages exceeding this limit fail silently and end up in the delivery queue where they retry indefinitely but never succeed.\n\nThis affects **both** send paths:\n- Auto-reply (`reply-dispatcher.ts`) — streaming reply dispatch\n- Message tool (`outbound.ts`) — `message` action / `sendText` / `sendPayload`\n\n## Solution\n\nExtended `shouldUseCard()` (which was duplicated in both files) to also count markdown tables and reject card mode when the count exceeds 5. Tables inside fenced code blocks are excluded from the count since they render as code, not as table components.\n\nWhen card mode is rejected, the message falls back to post mode, which uses `convertMarkdownTables(text, \"code\")` to convert tables to code blocks — a reliable, already existing code path.\n\n## Changes\n\n- `extensions/feishu/src/reply-dispatcher.ts`: Extended `shouldUseCard()` to check table count before choosing card mode\n- `extensions/feishu/src/outbound.ts`: Same change, applied at both card-decision points (`sendOutboundText` and `sendText`)\n\n## Testing\n\n- Verified that 5 tables → card mode (works)\n- Verified that 6 tables → API returns `ErrCode: 11310` (confirmed hard limit is exactly 5)\n- Verified that 7 tables → falls back to post mode, message delivered successfully\n- Verified that tables inside fenced code blocks are excluded from count\n\n## Backward Compatibility\n\n- No change for messages with ≤5 tables\n- No change for `renderMode: \"card\"` (explicit)\n- No change for messages without tables",
        "branch": "fix/feishu-card-table-limit",
